main event: A family observed an unidentified flying object over Fonculac, Minnesota for approximately 15 minutes.
interesting points: The object was described as a silvery, cigar-shaped craft with straight wings, measuring approximately 60 to 70 feet in wingspan., The object displayed red and green lights at the ends and white lights in the center, emitting a fluorescent glow., The object was visually observed with no optical aids and made no sound., The sighting occurred at dusk on 17 August 1966., There was no significant temperature inversion or known astronomical activity in the area during the observation.
sighted object: a silvery cigar-shaped craft with lights
witness description: Rowland Redstennin, his wife Elaine, and their daughters, Bonnie and Lana.
